Moving the bottleneck to Avatar of Water just moves the pointless camp to another zone, which they already tried and screwed up on.  Then they would still get CS petitions out the wazoo because as it stands now, first cleric hands in orbs and then gets reward and AoW poofs.  Well, as buggy as crap is in EQ... I'll bet money that if a 2nd cleric or in this case if bottleneck is moved to AoW then the 40 clerics all trying to race to turn in orb to AoW someone is gonna get their orb eaten.<br>
<br>
Having a bottleneck on Cleric epic is pretty lame anyway.  It doesnt let anyone do massive damage... ala Rogue epic compared to comperable Kunark release Rogue weapons, and even today, how many rogues do you see with FreeBringer bagged?  Some but not a large percentage.  No, what Watersprinkler does is eliminate downtime and let guilds/groups actually recover from a wipeout/death and get back to having fun.  OMG cant have that, not in a game!! /gasp!    <br>
<br>
Get that into Dev teams head maybe your making progress.  Watersprinkler doesnt let a guild beat an encounter, unless they are 100% gimp and doing battle rez for some dumbass mob like Vindi or Statue.  Dont forget to take into account how many Clerics quit or take long extended breaks from the game because the Cleric class is generally extremely boring to play so that you can let others have lots of fun to play.  <br>
<br>
Make the minimum required level for epic 59 and remove all the bottle necks ENTIRELY.  Guess what, nothing affecting game mechanics will change except there wont be so many pissed off customers and miracle of miracles, the overall goal (or at least they claimed it was the goal) of less /petitions for KS'ing will actually be achieved.<br>
